{ When I began my career, my favorite opening variation was: } 1. e4 e5 2. Nf3
Nc6 3. Bc4
{ These moves initiate the 'Italian Game'. This is the starting position of the Italian Game. Besides the sound idea of developing a piece and preparing to castle Kingside, the thematic idea behind the Italian Game is to take clear aim at the f7-pawn and, by extension, Black's King. The Italian Game is a dangerous opening for Black and he has to navigate some tricky tactical lines. }
3... Bc5 { This is a reasonable move, as Black also develops his Bishop. } 4.
b4
{ The energetic pawn sacrifice 4 b4!? is known as the 'Evans Gambit'. As usual, the idea behind the gambit is to pick up a lead in development. From this position, White has four main options:   4.O-O  Brings his King to safety, which is quite reasonable, but the move isn't considered that dynamic. Black plays  4...Nf6  continuing a balanced game.   4.c3  Giuoco Piano   4.d4  Max Lange Attack }
4... Bxb4 { Black must accept the gambit.   4...Bb6  5.a4 } 5. c3
{ White attacks the Bishop in order to support the central thrust, d2-d4. }
5... Ba5 { 5...Bc5  6.d4 } 6. d4
{ White reveals his strategy. He wants to open up the center, anticipating that his development will bring him the superior game. }
6... exd4
{ Some theorists prefer   6...d6  7.Qb3  Qd7  as the correct defensive continuation.   If  6...Nxd4  7.Bxf7+  Kxf7  8.Nxe5+  Kf8  9.Qxd4   or  6...Nxd4  7.Nxe5  Ne6  8.Nxf7  Kxf7  9.Bxe6  Kxe6  10.Qd5+  Ke7  11.Qxa5 }
7. O-O dxc3
{ Black greedily captures all the morsels being offered. Black has captured three pawns, but his position is dangerously behind in development White quickly goes on the offensive: }
8. Qb3 Qf6 9. e5
{ With a move that is even stronger than  9.Bg5  White also gains a tempo.  9...Qg6 }
9... Qg6 { Black's Queen must now guard the f7-pawn. } 10. Nxc3 Nge7 11. Ba3
O-O 12. Rad1
{ White's development is a thing of beauty. His pieces are poised for central domination and Black's position is under a great deal of pressure. The two pawns are a heavy investment, but Black will almost certainly have to give back his material gains to neutralize White's pressure. This is another position with which you should challenge your friends, playing alternating sides. }
