{ initiates the Ruy Lopez Opening. It has long been held that White's third move puts the most pressure on Black's position. There is the constant threat of White's capturing the c6-Knight and snipping the e5-pawn. Black's earliest defenses include:     3...d6  @@StartBracket@@Steinitz Defense@@EndBracket@@   3...Nge7  @@StartBracket@@Cozio Defense@@EndBracket@@   3...Nf6  @@StartBracket@@Berlin Defense@@EndBracket@@   3...Nd4  @@StartBracket@@Bird Defense@@EndBracket@@   3...Bc5  @@StartBracket@@Classical Defense@@EndBracket@@   3...f5  @@StartBracket@@Schliemann Defense@@EndBracket@@ }
3... -- *

