{ Return now to the Ruy Lopez main line } 1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5
{ And now } 3... a6
{ This move, introduced by Paul Morphy @@StartBracket@@1837-84@@EndBracket@@, puts the question to White's Bishop of its intentions.   3...a6  is based upon the tactical resource  4.Bxc6  dxc6  5.Nxe5  Qd4!  , when Black recaptures the e-pawn under favorable circumstances. 'Morphy's Defense' has become the favored move for a century.White is faced with a choice: Should he trade his Bishop for a Knight, or should the Bishop retreat? }
