1. d4 d5 { By an overwhelming margin, White's favored second move is: } 2. c4
{ White immediately attacks the d5-pawn and threatens to capture and eliminate Black's center.   By commencing the 'Queen's Gambit', White hopes to entice Black into capturing the c4-pawn, and after a subsequent recapture, White would then have a lead in development.   The Queen's Gambit is shown in our current position. If White is allowed to play c4xd5 unimpeded, Black's center is destroyed. Black has several choices:     2...dxc4  @@StartBracket@@Queen's Gambit Accepted@@EndBracket@@   2...c6  @@StartBracket@@Slav Defense@@EndBracket@@   2...e6  @@StartBracket@@Queen's Gambit Declined@@EndBracket@@, the main line   2...Bf5  @@StartBracket@@Grau Variation@@EndBracket@@   2...Nc6  @@StartBracket@@Chigorin Defense@@EndBracket@@ }
2... -- *

