{ After } 1. d4 d5 2. c4 c6 3. Nc3 Nf6 4. Nf3 dxc4
{ Besides the Alapin Variation, White can sacrifice a pawn with } 5. e4
{ White doesn't prevent ...b7-b5 and instead grabs the center. } 5... b5 6. e5
{ This is called the 'Geller Gambit'. Play continues: } 6... Nd5 7. a4
{ White has a grip in the center but is a pawn behind. After a great deal of practice, theorists consider Black's position to be sound. }
