[White "4: Classical Queen Pawn Openings"]
[Black "Tartakover Variation"]
[Result "*"]

{ Chess theorists are evenly split between Tartakover and main line adherents. The 'Tartakover Variation' begins }
1. d4 d5 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Nf6 4. Bg5 Be7
{ Black prepares to quickly castle while breaking the pin on the f6-Knight. }
5. e3 O-O
{ White must make a fundamental decision. Does he intend to delay the development of his g1-Knight with moves such as   6.Qd2   6.Qc2  or   6.Rc1  - or simply develop the Knight? Each of these moves contains its own peculiarities and Black must be familiar with each of them.  Because developing the g1-Knight is the most natural, I'll follow that line:   6.Nf3  . This leaves Black with the choice of:  6...--   6...Ne4  @@StartBracket@@Lasker Defense@@EndBracket@@   6...h6  @@StartBracket@@Neo-Orthodox Defense@@EndBracket@@   6...b6  @@StartBracket@@Orthodox Defense@@EndBracket@@ }
6. -- *

