[Black "French Defense 3.Nc3 Variations"]
[Result "*"]

{ By far the most popular way to meet the French Defense, } 1. e4 e6 2. d4 d5
{ Is with } 3. Nc3
{ White develops a Knight and protects his e4-pawn. Black has four main moves: }
3... --
{ 3...dxe4  @@StartBracket@@Rubinstein Variation@@EndBracket@@   3...Bb4  @@StartBracket@@Winawer Variation@@EndBracket@@   3...Nf6  @@StartBracket@@Classical or Steinitz Variation@@EndBracket@@   3...Be7  @@StartBracket@@Seirawan Variation@@EndBracket@@.Once more, all of these choices are fascinating lines leading to positions that are rich in strategy and tactics. }
