[SetUp "1"]

{ Levenfish Attack: One popular attacking scheme for White is the 'Levenfish Attack': }
6. f4 { White threatens e4-e5, which Black immediately prevents. } 6... Nc6 7.
Nf3 Bg7 8. Bd3 O-O 9. O-O
{ This is a common position of the Levenfish Attack. White's attacking scheme is to play Qd1-e1-h4 in conjunction with f4-f5 and Bc1-h6. Black has to come up with a reaction. IF he plays }
9... b6
{ Black can try to distract White's pieces from the Kingside by playing a line like 9...b6   9...d5  10.e5  White will have a big advantage. Thus it is difficult for Black to make a meaningful counter in the center.   9...Bg4 }
10. Qe1 Nb4 11. Qh4 Nxd3 12. cxd3 Ba6
{ Practice has shown the position to be dynamically equal. } *

