4. Nf3
{ White calmly develops a Knight and chooses not to define the center just yet }
4... Bg7 { Now White must reveal his plans. } 5. Qb3
{ The Russian school of chess has done an amazing 'joint collaboration' on the following bottomless variation. White develops his Queen early in order to put pressure on Black's d5-pawn.   5.Bg5  Seirawan Variation }
5... dxc4 6. Qxc4 O-O 7. e4
{ These are the standard moves. White has achieved a classical pawn center but the premature development of his Queen means that Black can create all kinds of counter defenses. }
